content: Spent the last 4 days mastering Python's pandas library. It's like learning a new language but for data.
Connected with an old friend from college. He's into DeFi now. Got some great insights on blockchain's potential.
Set up a meeting with a mentor in quantitative trading next week. Time to get serious about my career direction.
Began sketching out a basic trading strategy using historical data. AI pattern recognition is the key.
Joined a local meetup for blockchain enthusiasts. Pitched my idea for a DeFi project. Got some positive feedback.
Had a breakthrough with my AI model. It accurately predicted a minor market shift. Small steps forward.
Reviewed my trading journal from the past year. Identified key mistakes. Learning from them is the first step to improvement.
Spent the weekend at a blockchain conference. Networked with some developers, got inspired by their projects.
Started coding my first smart contract. It's rudimentary, but it's a start. Python and Solidity are becoming my new best friends.
Got feedback on my smart contract from a mentor. He pointed out some security flaws I need to address.
My AI model now includes sentiment analysis. The results are promising. It's like the market is whispering its secrets to me.
Met with my mentor for our scheduled session. He gave me a book on quantitative finance. Time to dive in.
Just attended a virtual talk on ethical AI in finance. Got me thinking about the moral implications of my work.
Refined my trading strategy with new AI insights. It's not perfect, but it's a step closer to my niche in quantitative trading.
